The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Paris. Stock
symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices are
from the last close.  Franceâ€™s benchmark  CAC 40 Index (CAC)  rose 1.6 percent to
3,176.19 points, the first advance in 12 days.  Acanthe Developpement SA (ACAN)  : The real-estate company
said second-quarter sales fell to 3.17 million euros from 3.89
million euros a year earlier, hurt by a decline in its office
and hotel businesses. The shares fell 1.8 percent to 1.11 euros.  Atari SA (ATA)  : The video-game maker whose titles
include Rollercoaster Tycoon said it completed the sale of its
unit Cryptic Studios Inc. for about 35 million euros in cash.
The shares rose 2.1 percent to 1.47 euros.  Eurazeo (RF)  : The investment company whose biggest
shareholder is Credit Agricole SA said it refinanced a 1-billion
euro syndicated credit line. The shares rose 2.9 percent to
37.44 euros.  Maisons France Confort (MFC)  : The home-builder said
first-half sales rose 51 percent to 307.4 million euros. The
shares fell 2.5 percent to 24.2 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
